{{Infobox Figure Skating Competition | title = 2001 Polish Figure Skating Championships | image = | imagesize = | caption = | comptype = National Championship | startdate = December 15 | enddate = December 17 | skatingseason = 2000-2001 | location = {{Flagicon|POL}} [[Warsaw]] | host = | venue = [[Torwar II]] | prizemoney = | championmen = [[Robert Grzegorczyk]] | championladies = [[Sabina Wojtala]] | championpairs = ''no competition'' | championdance = [[Sylwia Nowak]] & [[Sebastian Kolasiński]] | previouscomp = [[2000 Polish Figure Skating Championships]] | nextcomp = [[2002 Polish Figure Skating Championships]] }}
The '''2001 Polish Figure Skating Championships''' ({{lang-pl|Mistrzostwa Polski w łyżwiarstwie figurowym 2000/2001}}) were the [[Polish Figure Skating Championships]] of the 2000/2001 [[figure skating season]]. The Polish Championships are held annually to determine the National Champions of [[Poland]]. They were held in [[Warsaw]], between December 15 and December 17, 2000.
