{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}} {{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Bugti Stadium | nickname = Racecourse Ground | image = | caption = | country = Pakistan | location = [[Quetta]], Pakistan | tenants = [[Baluchistan cricket team]], [[Quetta cricket team]], [[Quetta Gladiators]], Pakistan | coordinates = | establishment = 1954 | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | international = true | onlyodidate = 30 October | onlyodiyear = 1996 | onlyodihome = Pakistan | onlyodiaway = Zimbabwe | club1 = | year1 = | date = 1 January 2017 | source = http://www.espncricinfo.com/pakistan/content/ground/58996.html Cricinfo }}
The '''Bugti Stadium''', formerly known as the '''Racecourse Ground''', is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Quetta]], Pakistan. The first recorded match on the ground was on 29 October 1954.<ref name="Cricinfo">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/columns/content/ground/58996.html |title=Bugti Stadium |accessdate=16 September 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref> It was used as a venue for a [[One Day International]] match between Pakistan and Zimbabwe in [[Zimbabwean cricket team in Pakistan in 1996–97|October 1996]].<ref name="ODI">{{Cite web |subscription=yes |url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/22/1537_o.html |title=One-Day International Matches played on Bugti Stadium, Quetta |accessdate=16 September 2016 |work=Cricket Archive}}</ref> Between 1954 and 2008 the ground hosted twenty-two [[first-class cricket|first-class]] matches.<ref name="FC">{{Cite web |subscription=yes |url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/22/1537_f.html |title=First-Class Matches played on Bugti Stadium, Quetta |accessdate=16 September 2016 |work=Cricket Archive}}</ref> It also hosted matches in the [[2016–17 Quaid-e-Azam Trophy]].<ref name="Quaid">{{Cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/1047837.html |title=Pool A: Peshawar v Habib Bank Limited at Quetta, Oct 1-4, 2016 |accessdate=16 September 2016 |work=ESPN Cricinfo}}</ref>
==Name== Until 1989, the Bugti Stadium was known as the Racecourse Ground.
