'''Melina Debora Sirolli''' (born 23 April 1984) was an Argentine female [[artistic gymnast]], representing her nation at international competitions. 

At the [[Gymnastics at the 1998 South American Games|1998 South American Games]], she won two gold medals, one silver, and two bronze. At the [[Gymnastics at the 1999 Pan American Games|1999 Pan American Games]], she won a bronze medal in the [[balance beam]] event.

Sirolli also participated at the [[Gymnastics at the 2000 Summer Olympics|2000 Summer Olympics]], the [[2003 World Artistic Gymnastics Championships]],<ref>{{cite web |title=2003 World Gymnastics Championships athletes - Melina Debora Sirolli |url=http://gym.longinestiming.com/File/000002030000FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF01 |work=longinestiming.com |date= |accessdate=27 January 2016}}</ref> and the [[Gymnastics at the 2003 Pan American Games|2003 Pan American Games]].

At the [[2008 Pan American Trampoline and Tumbling Championships]], she won a silver medal in the [[tumbling (gymnastics)|tumbling]] team event.

